history.content: I can only reliably comment about 172 which I am currently taking: it is a good class and I highly recommend if you're interested in computability or complexity theory and enjoyed 170 (I also highly recommend math 136, but only if you love proofs and want a pure math perspective on computability/decidability). 172 doesn't really rely on 170 imo but it definitely helps, so I say take it if you can. From what I hear about 270 it seems like a much harder/mathematical 170 but I think plenty of undergrads actually take it, so you should be able to as well. Good luck!

children.subject: Not sure what you mean by that, but for reference I got an A- in 170 and so far in 172 I scored below avg on the midterm but have done fairly well on the homeworks and I think 172 makes more sense to me than 170. It's a pretty self-selecting class as there are about 800 students in 170 but only 60 in 172.
